famous.name: Lame Horse open back banjo
famous.description: This is about a ten year old Lame Horse banjo made by luthier Chris Jenkins in Texas. https://lamehorse.net/ He builds very fancy and quite expensive guitars ($7000 +) and occasionally does a banjo. I bought this one new directly from Chris at the luthiers convention in Santa Rose about ten years ago. It is an open back banjo with a 12 block style maple pot and neck.  It is very loud and bright sounding. It has a frailing scoop and a single coordinator rod, five piece neck and has a very easy action. Quite ornamental with exotic woods and inlay up and down the neck. It is in excellent condition with no damage. Mary Cox has hers for sale currently for $2300  plus shipping from Florida on the Banjo Hangout. She is famous, I am not. Reasonable offers accepted, forget low ballers as I do not need to sell it. Comes with a sturdy bump case. No trades, cash only.
